# Constitution: Pre-commit Enforcement — lint, type-check, then tests, in
# that order, before a commit is accepted. Bypassing (git commit --no-verify)
# is prohibited except in a documented emergency, and any bypass must be
# followed immediately by a commit that re-establishes the passing state.
# (End-to-end/axe tests run in CI, not here, to keep the hook fast.)
#
# The test step runs the coverage ratchet (constitution Quality Standard):
# the same never-decrease line-coverage gate CI enforces, run here so a
# drop is caught before the push rather than after. `coverage:ratchet`
# runs the full unit suite with coverage, so it replaces a plain `test`
# rather than adding a second run.
npm run lint
npm run check
npm run coverage:ratchet
